    <div class="row">
        <div class="span4 feature1">
            <h2>Sass + Compass</h2>
            <p>Tired of <a href="http://compass-style.org/reference/compass/css3/">writing vendor prefixes</a>, <a href="http://compass-style.org/help/tutorials/spriting/">making image sprites</a>? Love Sass/Compass but hate command line interface? Fire has Sass/Compass support.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="span4 feature2">
            <h2>LiveReload Support</h2>
            <p>Stop refresh your browsers! Fire has LiveReload support, so you don't have to press the refresh button.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="span4 feature3">
            <h2>Template languages</h2>
            <p>You can code in Haml/ERB/Markdown, and get HTML from our built-in web server. You can even use layouts, partials, and helpers to code even faster.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
